    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="832"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d832">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.20/3.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 13, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s January 10. Liberian President submitted Department’s proposition to
                    Legislature and obtained its approval as to <pb facs="0780" n="664"
                        xml:id="pg_664"/> number of ex-noncommissioned officers for border police
                    and amount of their respective salaries with housing.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crum</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
